# data_contracts.me
# Purpose: Authoritative entity structures, required fields, enums, relationships,
#          and query field requirements. Any model in iOS or Android must conform to
#          these definitions. Deviations cause silent decode failures.
# Scope: iOS Models.swift, Android data layer, Supabase PostgREST queries

---

## 1. CRITICAL QUERY RULE

PostgREST only returns columns you explicitly enumerate in `select=`. Omitting a column
causes silent nil decode — no error is thrown. This has caused production bugs.

**Every column listed in the entity definitions below must appear in all query strings
for that table.** Adding a new column to a model without adding it to all query strings
will silently decode as nil.

---

## 2. CORE ENTITIES

### `clubs`
Required columns in ALL select strings (5 query strings in SupabaseService):
`fetchClubs`, `fetchClubDetail`, `createClub`, `updateClubOwnerFields`, delete helper

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID PK | |
| name | TEXT | Sanitise: max length cap + no raw URL injection |
| description | TEXT NULL | |
| address | TEXT NULL | |
| latitude | FLOAT8 NULL | **MUST appear in all 5 select strings** — omission silently breaks NearbyDiscoveryView |
| longitude | FLOAT8 NULL | **MUST appear in all 5 select strings** |
| image_url | TEXT NULL | Custom upload URL or preset key |
| custom_banner_url | TEXT NULL | Owner-uploaded banner; falls back to preset |
| created_by | UUID FK → auth.users | Club owner |
| subscription_tier | TEXT DEFAULT 'free' | Denormalised; values: `free`, `starter`, `pro`, `enterprise` |
| stripe_connect_id | TEXT NULL | Denormalised from `club_stripe_accounts` |
| membership_policy | TEXT | Membership join behaviour |
| created_at | TIMESTAMPTZ | |

Sanitisation at decode time (DB-authoritative — migration `20260429_field_length_constraints.sql`):
- The DB enforces CHECK constraints. Client-side trimming is UX polish only — never define different limits.
- `image_url`: validate URL scheme against allowed Supabase host OR preset key
- DO NOT pass unbounded text fields directly into UI models

Field length limits (DB CHECK constraints, Android must respect the same values):

| Column | Max (chars) | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `name` | 120 | required |
| `description` | 2000 | |
| `contact_email` | 320 | |
| `contact_phone` | 30 | |
| `website` | 260 | |
| `manager_name` | 160 | |
| `suburb` | 80 | |
| `state` | 80 | |
| `venue_name` | 260 | also applies to `club_venues.venue_name` |

`club_venues` inherits the same `suburb` (80) and `state` (80) limits.

### `games`
Required in ALL 8 game select strings:

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID PK | |
| club_id | UUID FK → clubs | |
| title | TEXT | |
| date_time | TIMESTAMPTZ | |
| duration_minutes | INT | |
| max_spots | INT | |
| skill_level | TEXT | Enum: `all`, `beginner`, `intermediate`, `advanced` — NO `tournament` |
| fee_amount | INT | 0 = free |
| currency | TEXT DEFAULT 'aud' | |
| platform_fee_bps | INT DEFAULT 1000 | Basis points (1000 = 10%) |
| cancellation_window_hours | INT DEFAULT 6 | Hours before game start |
| publish_at | TIMESTAMPTZ NULL | NULL = published; future = scheduled/hidden |
| created_by | UUID FK → auth.users | |
| venue_name | TEXT NULL | |
| latitude | FLOAT8 NULL | |
| longitude | FLOAT8 NULL | |
| notes | TEXT NULL | |
| created_at | TIMESTAMPTZ | |

Games field limits (DB CHECK constraints):
- `title`: 1–200 chars (non-empty, ≤ 200)
- `max_spots`: 2–64 (when not null)
- `court_count`: 1–50 (when not null)

Computed properties (client-side only):
- `isScheduled: Bool` = `publishAt != nil && publishAt > now()`
- `startsInPast: Bool` = `dateTime < now()`
- `spotsLeft: Int` = `maxSpots - confirmedCount`
- `spotsFilled: Bool` = `spotsLeft <= 0`

