### `profiles`
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID PK = auth.uid() | |
| full_name | TEXT NULL | max 200 chars |
| email | TEXT NULL | |
| phone | TEXT NULL | max 30 chars |
| emergency_contact_name | TEXT NULL | max 160 chars |
| emergency_contact_phone | TEXT NULL | max 30 chars |
| dupr_id | TEXT NULL | 6–24 chars, `^[A-Z0-9-]+$` + must contain digit; server-enforced |
| dupr_rating | NUMERIC(5,3) NULL | 2.000–8.000, exactly 3 decimal places; server-enforced via column type + CHECK |
| skill_level | TEXT NULL | |
| stripe_customer_id | TEXT NULL | Reused across clubs for subscription billing |
| created_at | TIMESTAMPTZ | |

Profiles field limits (DB CHECK constraints — migrations `20260429_field_length_constraints.sql`, `20260429_dupr_validation_constraints.sql`, `20260429_dupr_rating_3dp_precision.sql`):
- `full_name`: ≤ 200 chars
- `phone`: ≤ 30 chars
- `emergency_contact_name`: ≤ 160 chars
- `emergency_contact_phone`: ≤ 30 chars
- `dupr_id`: 6–24 chars, uppercase alphanumeric + hyphen only (`^[A-Z0-9-]+$`), must contain at least one digit (when not null). **Always PATCH uppercase.** DB rejects lowercase.
- `dupr_rating`: column type `NUMERIC(5,3)` — exactly 3 decimal places always. Range 2.000–8.000 inclusive (when not null). **Android must send exactly 3dp** (e.g. `3.524`, never `3.52` or `3`). Do not cap silently — reject input and show error. Required by DUPR API integration.

